From edgar pearlstein Subject Waco information accuracy It should be remembered that all of the first reports came from the FBI and that independent observers the press were not allowed to get close and see things for Official communiques tend to be self serving for the agencies that issue People in general tend to believe first reports as these get the most and the biggest Corrections are often An example is the FBI report that several of the bodies found in the rubble had bullet The local coroner who is independent of the FBI has so far found no bullet wounds